  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Oral carvedilol administered in escalating doses in patients with atrial fibrillation among
      patients with AF with fast ventricular rate.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with AF with FVR of any etiology were evaluated and given escalating doses of oral
      carvedilol in doses - 3.125mg OD, then 3.125 bid, then 6.25mg bid, then 12.5mg bid. The ECG
      was recorded regularly and analysed for rate reduction or control.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
